        <headline>Flood Advisory issued August 22 at 2:20PM EDT until August 22 at 4:00PM EDT by NWS Charleston SC</headline>
        <description>* WHAT...Flooding caused by excessive rainfall continues.

* WHERE...A portion of southeast South Carolina, including the
following counties, Charleston and Colleton.

* WHEN...Until 400 PM EDT.

* IMPACTS...Minor flooding in low-lying and poor drainage areas.

* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...
- At 218 PM EDT, Doppler radar indicated thunderstorms with
torrential extending from Bennetts Point to Edisto Beach. As
much as 1 to 4 inches of rain has fallen across parts of
lower Charleston County today. An additional 1 to 2 inches
could fall through 4 PM. The risk for minor flooding of low-
lying and poor drainage areas continues.
- Some locations that will experience flooding include...
Edisto Beach, Hollywood, Ravenel, Seabrook Island, Meggett,
Rockville, Bears Bluff, Adams Run, Edisto Island and Yonges
Island.
</description>
        <instruction>Turn around, don't drown when encountering flooded roads. Most flood
deaths occur in vehicles.</instruction>
